item.description:
Update Repositories Script This script recursively finds all git repositories in a specified directory and pulls the latest changes for each one.
Prerequisites  Bash shell Git installed Proper permissions to access and modify the repositories  Installation   Create the script: Save the following script to a file named update_repos.sh:
#!/bin/bash  # Define the default root directory where your repos are located DEFAULT_ROOT_DIR=&#34;/home/cobra/Repos&#34; # Use the provided argument as the root directory, or the default if none is provided ROOT_DIR=${1:-$DEFAULT_ROOT_DIR} echo &#34;Starting update process for repositories in $ROOT_DIR&#34; # Function to pull changes in a git repository pull_repo() { local repo_dir=$1 echo &#34;Pulling updates in $repo_dir&#34; cd &#34;$repo_dir&#34; || return git pull echo &#34;Completed update in $repo_dir&#34; cd - || return } # Export the function so it can be used by find -exec export -f pull_repo # Find all .
